{"parse":{"title":"table","pageid":38559,"redirects":[],"wikitext":"{{also|Table|tablé}}\n==English==\n{{was wotd|2015|February|11}}\n\n===Alternative forms===\n* {{alt|en|tyebble||Geordie}}\n\n===Etymology===\n{{multiple images\n|direction = vertical\n|image1 = Table.png\n|caption1 = A table (furniture)\n|image2 = Arabischesalphabet.svg\n|caption2 = A table of characters in the Arabic alphabet\n}}\n\n{{inh+|en|enm|table}}, {{m|enm|tabel}}, {{m|enm|tabil}}, {{m|enm|tabul}}, from {{inh|en|ang|tabele}}, {{m|ang|tabul}}, {{m|ang|tablu}}, {{m|ang|tabule}}, {{m|ang|tabula||board}}; also as {{m|ang|tæfl}}, {{m|ang|tæfel}}, an early {{uder|en|gem|-}} borrowing of {{der|en|la|tabula||tablet, board, plank, chart}}. The sense of “piece of furniture” is from {{der|en|fro|table}}, of same Latin origin; Old English used {{m|ang|bēod}} or {{m|ang|bord}} instead for this meaning: ''see'' {{m|en|board}}. {{doublet|en|tabula|tavla}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{enPR|tāʹbəl}}, {{IPA|en|/ˈteɪbl̩/}}\n** {{IPA|en|[ˈt(ʰ)eɪbɫ̩]|a=RP}}\n*** {{audio|en|En-uk-table.ogg|a=RP}}\n** {{IPA|en|[ˈtʰeɪb(ə)ɫ]|a=US}}\n*** {{audio|en|En-us-table.ogg|a=GA}}\n** {{IPA|en|[ˈtʰæɪbəɫ]|a=AU}}\n*** {{audio|en|en-au-table.ogg|a=AU}}\n** {{IPA|en|[ˈtʰeːb(ə)ɫ]|a=CA}}\n*** {{IPA|en|[ˈtɛːb(ə)ɫ]|a=dialectal}}\n* {{rhymes|en|eɪbəl|s=2}}\n* {{hyph|en|ta|ble}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{en-noun}}\n\n# {{sid|en|Q14748}}{{lb|en|countable}} Furniture with a top surface to accommodate a variety of uses.\n## An item of [[furniture]] with a [[flat]] [[top]] [[surface]] raised above the ground, usually on one or more legs.\n##: {{ux|en|Set that dish on the '''table''' over there, please.}}\n##* {{RQ:Lincoln Pratt's Patients|chapter=6|passage=He had one hand on the bounce bottle—and he'd never let go of that since he got back to the '''table'''—but he had a handkerchief in the other and was swabbing his deadlights with it.}}\n##* {{RQ:Allingham China Governess|chapter=Foreword|passage=A very neat old woman, still in her good outdoor coat and best beehive hat, was sitting at a polished mahogany '''table''' on whose surface there were several scored scratches so deep that a triangular piece of the veneer had come cleanly away,{{nb...}}.}}\n## The [[board]] or table-like [[furniture]] on which a [[game]] is played, such as [[snooker]], [[billiards]]{{,}} or [[draughts]].\n## A flat [[tray]] which can be used as a table.\n## A supply of food or entertainment.\n##: {{ux|en|The baron kept a fine '''table''' and often held large banquets.}}\n## {{lb|en|metonym}} A [[booth]] or [[display]] at an event such as an [[exposition]] or fair.\n## A service of [[Holy Communion]].\n## {{lb|en|backgammon}} One [[half]] of a [[backgammon]] [[board]], which is divided into the inner and outer table.\n## A [[wide]], [[flat]] [[obstacle]] for a [[horse]] to jump over.\n# A group of people at a table, for example, for a meal, meeting or game.\n#* {{RQ:Shakespeare Hamlet|V|i|278|1|Alas poore ''Yorick'' {{...}} VVhere be your Jibes now? Your Gambals? Your Songs? Your flaſhes of Merriment that were wont to ſet the '''Table''' on a Rore?}}\n#* {{RQ:Churchill Celebrity|chapter=8|passage=The humor of my proposition appealed more strongly to Miss Trevor than I had looked for, and from that time forward she became her old self again;{{...}}. Our '''table''' in the dining-room became again the abode of scintillating wit and caustic repartee, Farrar bracing up to his old standard, and the demand for seats in the vicinity rose to an animated competition.}}\n## {{lb|en|poker|metonym}} The [[lineup]] of players at a given table.\n##: {{ux|en|That's the strongest '''table''' I've ever seen at a European Poker Tour event}}\n## {{lb|en|RPG|metonym}} A group of players meeting regularly to play a [[campaign]].\n## {{lb|en|waitstaff|metonym}} A group of diners at a given table or tables.\n##: {{ux|en|'''Table''' 9 wants another round of beers.}}\n##: {{ux|en|John always gets the best tips because he gets the best '''tables'''! It's not fair!}}\n# A two-dimensional presentation of data.\n## A [[matrix]] or [[grid]] of [[data]] arranged in [[row]]s and [[column]]s.\n##* {{quote-book|en|year=1997|author=Chris Horrocks|title=Introducing Foucault|page=69|publisher=Totem Books, Icon Books|isbn=1840460865\n|passage=I’m using mathesis — a universal science of measurement and order …<br/>And there is also taxinomia a principle of classification and ordered tabulation.<br/>Knowledge replaced universal resemblance with finite differences. History was arrested and turned into '''tables''' …<br/>Western reason had entered the age of judgement.}}\n## A collection of [[arithmetic]] calculations arranged in a table, such as [[multiplication]]s in a [[multiplication table]].\n##: {{ux|en|The children were practising multiplication '''tables'''.}}\n##: {{ux|en|Don’t you know your '''tables'''?}}\n##: {{ux|en|Here is a '''table''' of natural logarithms.}}\n## {{lb|en|computing|chiefly|databases}} A [[lookup table]], most often a set of [[vector]]s.\n## {{lb|en|sports}} A visual representation of a classification of teams or individuals based on their success over a predetermined period.\n##* {{quote-journal|en|date=April 10, 2011|author=Alistair Magowan|work=BBC Sport\n|title=[http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport2/hi/football/eng_prem/9446263.stm Aston Villa 1-0 Newcastle]\n|passage=On this evidence they will certainly face tougher tests, as a depleted Newcastle side seemed to bask in the relative security of being ninth in the '''table'''.}}\n# {{lb|en|musical instruments}} The top of a stringed instrument, particularly a member of the [[violin]] family: the side of the instrument against which the strings vibrate.\n# The [[flat]] [[topmost]] [[facet]] of a [[cut]] [[diamond]].\n# A [[flat]] [[gravestone]] supported on [[pillar]]s.\n# {{lb|en|obsolete|biblical}} A [[writing]] [[tablet]].\n\n====Synonyms====\n* {{sense|computing}} {{l|en|grid}}, {{l|en|vector}}\n\n====Hypernyms====\n* {{sense|computing}} {{l|en|array}}\n* {{sense|furniture}} {{l|en|furniture}}\n\n====Hyponyms====\n{{col4|en|title=furniture\n|bar table\n|billiard table|wall table|by-table\n|bedside table\n|bench table\n|bird table\n|book table\n|captain's table\n|chart table\n|chef's table\n|children's table\n|cocktail table\n|coffee table|conference table\n|console table|loo table\n|dining table|gateleg table\n|dinner table\n|drafting table\n|drawing table\n|dressing table\n|drinks table\n|drop-leaf table\n|end table\n|examination table\n|extension table\n|fire table\n|frame table\n|gaming table\n|green table\n|gypsy table\n|high table\n|hobby table\n|imposing table\n|inversion table\n|kiddie table\n|light table\n|massage table\n|milking table\n|Morrison table\n|nature table\n|negotiating table\n|negotiation table\n|night table\n|Noguchi table\n|occasional table\n|operating table\n|Parsons table\n|Pembroke table\n|picnic table\n|pier table\n|ping-pong table\n|pintable\n|pool table|change table|kitchen table\n|racetrack table\n|refectory table\n|retable\n|roller table\n|rotary table\n|round table|peanut table\n|sand table\n|self-waiting table\n|shuffleboard table\n|side table\n|sitting table\n|sleeping table\n|slime table\n|snooker table\n|sofa table\n|sorting table\n|spider table\n|steam table\n|swing table\n|table tennis table|diaper table|nappy table|tea table\n|table of death\n|throwing table\n|toilet table\n|toning table\n|tray-table\n|trestle table\n|trivet table\n|vanity table\n|vaulting table\n|wall table\n|washhand table\n|whirling table\n|Wilfley table\n|worktable|card table|folding table\n}}\n\n{{col2|en|title=geology\n|water table\n}}\n\n{{col4|en|title=two-dimensional enlisting\n|cap table|capitalization table\n|Cayley table\n|concentration table\n|contingency table\n|data table\n|division table\n|experience table\n|factorial table\n|file allocation table\n|function table\n|hash table\n|high-score table\n|ICE table\n|input-output table\n|life table\n|league table\n|log table\n|lookup table\n|medal table\n|mortality table\n|multiplication table\n|pay table\n|periodic table\n|rainbow table\n|RICE table\n|shake table\n|subtable|supertable\n|table of contents\n|tide table\n|time table\n|times table\n|traverse table\n|truth table\n}}\n\n====Coordinate terms====\n* {{sense|furniture}} {{l|en|chair}}\n\n====Derived terms====\n{{col4|en|at table\n|table header\n|bottom of the table\n|bring to the table\n|style-table\n|above the table|head of the table\n|clear the table\n|coffee table book,coffee-table book\n|corbel table\n|crosstable\n|dispatch table\n|distributed hash table\n|down-table\n|drink under the table\n|entable\n|extension table\n|fact table|cool kids' table\n|farm-to-table\n|fence the tables\n|hashtable\n|kitchen table issue\n|kitchen table polyamory\n|kitchen-table software\n|kitchen table software\n|lay one's cards on the table\n|lay the table\n|Lord's table\n|metatable\n|midtable\n|multitable\n|mutating table\n|off the table\n|on the table\n|open table\n|page table\n|piece table| table sauce|table-ender\n|pivot table\n|pizza table\n|place one's cards on the table\n|plane table\n|pound the table\n|put bread on the table\n|put food on the table\n|put one's cards on the table\n|readtable\n|read the table\n|run the table\n|seat at the table\n|set the table\n|soundtable\n|sound table\n|sparse table\n|speed table\n|symbol table\n|table apple\n|tablebase\n|Table Bay\n|table beer\n|table beet\n|table bell\n|table bird\n|table board\n|table boarder\n|tablebook\n|table centre\n|tablecloth\n|table-cloth\n|table cloth\n|table cracker\n|table dance\n|table dancer\n|table dancing\n|table-decker\n|table decoration\n|table d'hote\n|table d'hôte\n|table diamond\n|table-diamond\n|table drain\n|table drink\n|tablefellow\n|table football\n|tableful\n|table game\n|tablegrape\n|table grape\n|table head\n|table hockey\n|tablehood\n|table-hop\n|table-hopper\n|table hymn\n|tableity\n|table knife\n|table lamp\n|tableland\n|tableless\n|table lighter\n|tablelike\n|table-linen\n|table line