n* Mongolian:\n*: Cyrillic: {{t+|mn|хүрд}}\n*: Mongolian script: {{t|mn|ᠬᠦᠷᠳ᠋}}\n* Norwegian:\n*: Bokmål: {{tt|nb|tabell|m}}\n* Polish: {{tt+|pl|tabela|f}}\n* Portuguese: {{tt+|pt|tabela|f}}\n* Romanian: {{tt+|ro|tabelă|f}}, {{tt+|ro|tabel|n}}\n* Russian: {{tt+|ru|табли́ца|f}}, {{tt|ru|[[та́блица]] [[умножение|умноже́ния]]|f}} {{q|multiplication table}}\n* Scottish Gaelic: {{tt|gd|bòrd|m}}, {{tt|gd|clàr|m}}\n* Slovak: {{tt|sk|tabuľka|m}}\n* Spanish: {{tt+|es|tablas|f-p}}\n* Swahili: {{tt+|sw|meza}}\n* Swedish: {{tt+|sv|tabell|c}}\n* Tagalog: {{tt|tl|talahanayan}}\n* Tamil: {{t+|ta|வாய்பாடு}}\n* Turkish: {{tt+|tr|cetvel}}, {{tt+|tr|tablo}}\n* Ukrainian: {{tt|uk|табли́ця|f}}\n* Urdu: {{t|ur|پَہاڑا|m}}\n* Vietnamese: {{tt+|vi|bảng}} ({{tt|vi|榜}}), {{tt|vi|bảng kế}}, {{tt+|vi|biểu}} ({{tt+|vi|表}})\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n{{trans-top|computing: a lookup table}}\n* Afrikaans: {{t|af|tabel}}\n* Armenian: {{tt+|hy|աղյուսակ}}\n* Assamese: {{tt|as|তালিকা}}\n* Bulgarian: {{t+|bg|таблица|f}}\n* Greek: {{tt+|el|πίνακας|m}}, {{tt+|el|ευρετήριο|n}}\n* Hindi: {{tt+|hi|तालिका|f}}\n* Japanese: {{tt+|ja|配列|tr=はいれつ, hairetsu}}, {{t+|ja|テーブル|tr=tēburu}}\n* Korean: {{tt+|ko|테이블}}\n* Russian: {{tt+|ru|табли́ца|f}}\n* Swahili: {{tt+|sw|meza}}, {{tt+|sw|meza}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n{{trans-top|music: the top of a stringed instrument}}\n* Bulgarian: {{t-needed|bg}}\n* Finnish: {{tt+|fi|kansi}}\n* Swahili: {{tt+|sw|meza}}\n}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n{{checktrans-top}}\n* Hmong:\n*: Hmong Don: {{t-check|hmf|rooj}}<!--was in the \"item of furniture\" section-->\n* Indonesian: {{t+check|id|meja}}\n* Italian: {{t+check|it|tavola|f}} {{q|2}}, {{t+check|it|tavolo|m}} {{q|1}}\n* Latin: {{t-check|la|tabula|f}} {{q|2,3,4}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n====References====\n* {{pedia}}\n\n===Verb===\n{{en-verb}}\n\n# {{senseid|en|tabulate}} To [[tabulate]]; to put into a table or grid. {{defdate|from 15th c.}}\n#: {{ux|en|to '''table''' fines}}\n# {{senseid|en|give food to}} {{lb|en|now|rare}} To supply (a guest, client etc.) with [[food]] at a table; to [[feed]]. {{defdate|from 15th c.}}\n#* ''''April 13 1638''', {{w|Henry Wotton}}, ''letter to John Milton''\n#*: At Siena I was '''tabled''' in the house of one Alberto Scipioni\n# {{senseid|en|depict}} {{lb|en|obsolete}} To [[delineate]]; to [[represent]], as in a picture; to [[depict]]. {{defdate|17th–19th c.}}\n#* '''c. 1607''', {{w|Francis Bacon}}, letter to {{w|Tobie Matthew}}\n#*: '''tabled''' and pictured in the chambers of meditation\n# {{senseid|en|add to the agenda}} {{lb|en|non-US}} To put on the table of a commission or legislative assembly; to propose for formal [[discussion]] or [[consideration]], to put on the agenda. {{defdate|from 17th c.}}\n#: {{syn|en|moot<id:bring up for debate>|propose#Verb}}\n#* {{quote-journal|en|date=16 January 2019|author=Heather Stewart; Daniel Boffey|journal=The Guardian\n|passage=In a raucous Commons, the Labour leader, Jeremy Corbyn, confirmed he had '''tabled''' a formal motion of confidence in the government, backed by other opposition leaders, which MPs would vote on on Wednesday.}}\n# {{senseid|en|remove from the agenda}} {{lb|en|chiefly|US}} To remove from the agenda, to [[postpone]] dealing with; to [[shelve]] {{gloss|to indefinitely postpone consideration or discussion of something}}. {{defdate|from 19th c.}}\n#: {{ux|en|The legislature '''tabled''' the amendment, so they will not be discussing it until later.}}\n#: {{ux|en|The [[motion]] was '''tabled,''' ensuring that it would not be taken up until a later date.}}\n# {{lb|en|metonym}} To [[represent]] a company or organization (at an [[exposition]], fair, etc.), usually at a [[booth]] or [[display]].\n# {{senseid|en|join with coaks}} {{lb|en|carpentry|obsolete}} To [[join]] (pieces of timber) together using [[coak]]s. {{defdate|18th–19th c.}}\n# {{senseid|en|put onto a table}} To put on a table. {{defdate|from 19th c.}}\n#* '''1833''' {{w|Thomas Carlyle}}, letter to his Mother, ''The Correspondence of Thomas Carlyle and Ralph Waldo Emerson''\n#*: [A]fter some clatter offered us a rent of five pounds for the right to shoot here, and even '''tabled''' the cash that moment, and would not pocket it again.\n# {{lb|en|poker|colloquial}} To show one's cards face-up, especially during [[showdown]].\n# {{senseid|en|reinforce (sails)}} {{lb|en|nautical}} To make board [[hem#Etymology 2|hems]] in the skirts and bottoms of (sails) in order to strengthen them in the part attached to the [[bolt-rope]].\n\n====Related terms====\n* {{l|en|tabulate}}\n\n====Translations====\n{{trans-top|to put on a table}}\n* Basque: {{t-check|eu|[[mahai]] [[gainean]] [[jarri]]}} {{attention|eu|2=was \"[[mahai]] [[gainean]] [[jarri]]\" - assumed sum-of-parts; if an idiom, remove the wikilinks to the individual words. see [[User:So9q/Improved-xte.js/documentation#Translation_fixing]]}}\n* Bulgarian: {{t|bg|слагам масата}}\n* Dutch: {{t|nl|[[op]] [[tafel]] [[zetten]]}}, {{t-check|nl|[[de]] [[tafel]] [[dekken]]}} {{q|to prepare a table for a meal}}\n* Finnish: {{t|fi|[[panna]] [[pöytä|pöydälle]]}}\n* French: {{t+|fr|mettre la table}}\n* Italian: {{t+|it|presentare}}\n* Japanese: {{sense|to put an object on a table}} {{t|ja|テーブルに置く|tr=tēburu ni oku}}, {{sense|to prepare a table for a meal}} {{t|ja|食事の支度をする|tr=shokuji no shitaku wo suru}}\n* Norwegian: {{t|no|[[dekke]] ([[på]]) [[bordet]]}} {{q|to prepare a table for a meal}}\n* Portuguese: {{t+|pt|servir}}\n* Romanian: {{t|ro|a depune pe masă}}, {{t|ro|a pune masa}}\n* Spanish: {{t|es|[[poner]] [[sobre]] [[la]] [[mesa]]}}\n* Swahili: {{t+|sw|meza}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n{{trans-top|to propose for discussion}}\n* Bulgarian: {{t+|bg|представям}}\n* Dutch: {{t|nl|[[ter]] [[tafel]] [[brengen]]}}\n* Finnish: {{t|fi|[[tuoda]] [[keskustelu|keskusteluun]]}}, {{t|fi|[[nostaa]] [[pöytä|pöydälle]]}}\n* Italian: {{t+|it|proporre}}\n* Japanese: {{t|ja|議題にする|tr=gidai ni suru}}, {{t|ja|議題に上げる|tr=gidai ni ageru}}\n* Māori: {{t|mi|tāpae}}\n* Portuguese: {{t+|pt|propor}}\n* Spanish: {{t|es|[[traer]] [[a]] [[discusión]]}}\n* Swahili: {{t+|sw|meza}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n{{trans-top|to postpone a motion}}\n* Bulgarian: {{t-needed|bg}}\n* Finnish: {{t|fi|jättää pöydälle}}, {{t+|fi|pöydätä}}\n* Japanese: {{t|ja|棚上げにする|tr=tanaage ni suru}}\n* Portuguese: {{t+|pt|adiar}}\n* Swahili: {{t+|sw|meza}}\n* Swedish: {{t+|sv|bordlägga}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n{{trans-top|to postpone}}\n* Bulgarian: {{t+|bg|отлагам}}\n* Finnish: {{t|fi|[[siirtää]] [[myöhä|myöhemmäksi]]}}\n* Italian: {{t+|it|posporre}}\n* Japanese: {{t|ja|棚上げにする|tr=tanaage ni suru}}\n* Portuguese: {{t+|pt|adiar}}\n* Romanian: {{t+|ro|amâna}}\n* Swahili: {{t+|sw|meza}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n{{trans-top|to tabulate}}\n* Basque: {{t|eu|tabulatu}}\n* Bulgarian: {{t|bg|съставям таблица}}, {{t|bg|табулирам}}\n* Dutch: {{t|nl|tabelleren}}\n* Finnish: {{t+|fi|taulukoida}}\n* Japanese: {{t|ja|表を書く|tr=hyō wo kaku}}, {{t|ja|表組みする|tr=hyō-kumi suru}}, {{t|ja|作表する|tr=sakuhyō suru}}\n* Macedonian: {{t|mk|табели́ра}}\n* Portuguese: {{t+|pt|tabular}}\n* Spanish: {{t+|es|tabular}}\n* Swahili: {{t+|sw|meza}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n{{checktrans-top}}\n* Spanish: {{t+check|es|posponer}}\n* Swedish: {{t+check|sv|bordlägga}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n===See also===\n* {{l|en|tabula rasa}}\n\n===References===\n* {{pedia|table (parliamentary procedure)}}\n\n===Anagrams===\n* {{anagrams|en|a=abelt|ablet|Taleb|belta|blate|bleat}}\n\n{{cln|en|contranyms}}\n{{C|en|Furniture}}\n\n==French==\n{{wp|fr:}}\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{fr-IPA}}\n** {{audio|fr|Fr-table.ogg|a=France}}\n** {{audio|fr|LL-Q150 (fra)-DSwissK-table.wav|a=<<Switzerland>> (<<Valais>>)}}\n** {{audio|fr|LL-Q150 (fra)-Lepticed7-table.wav|a=<<France>> (<<Toulouse>>)}}\n** {{audio|fr|LL-Q150 (fra)-LoquaxFR-table.wav|a=<<France>> (<<Vosges>>)|IPA=[tab]}}\n** {{audio|fr|LL-Q150 (fra)-Mecanautes-table.wav|a=France}}\n** {{audio|fr|LL-Q150 (fra)-Poslovitch-table.wav|a=<<France>> (<<Vosges>>)}}\n** {{audio|fr|LL-Q150 (fra)-Jérémy-Günther-Heinz Jähnick-table.wav|a=<<France>> (<<Somain>>)}}\n** {{audio|fr|LL-Q150 (fra)-DenisdeShawi-table.wav|a=<<Canada>> (<<Shawinigan>>)|IPA=[tab]}}\n* {{rhymes|fr|abl|s=1}}\n\n===Etymology 1===\n{{inh+|fr|fro|table}}, from {{inh|fr|la|tabula||tablet}}. {{doublet|fr|tôle|taule}}.\n\n====Noun====\n{{fr-noun|f}}\n\n# {{tcl|fr|table|id=Q14748}}\n#: {{ux|fr|Pourquoi as-tu laissé ces livres sur la '''table''' ?|Why did you leave these books on the '''table'''?}}\n# [[flat]] [[surface]] atop various objects\n# flat part of a [[cut]] or [[carved]] object\n# {{lb|fr|music}} table of a stringed instrument\n# [[matrix]] or [[grid]] of [[data]] arranged in [[row]]s and [[column]]s\n# [[systematic]] [[list]] of [[content]]\n\n=====Derived terms=====\n{{col3|fr\n|à table\n|attabler\n|avoir table ouverte\n|bière de table\n|dessous-de-table\n|devoir sur table\n|entabler\n|hockey sur table\n|jouer cartes sur table\n|mettre la table\n|mettre ses couilles sur la table\n|mettre sur la table\n|ordinateur de table\n|passer sous la table\n|poser ses couilles sur la table\n|se mettre à table\n|sel de table\n|table à manger\n|table à repasser\n|table basse\n|table d'hôte\n|table de chevet\n|table de nuit\n|table de multiplication\n|table des matières\n|table des négociations\n|table rase\n|table ronde\n|tabler\n|taper du poing sur la table\n|tenir table ouverte\n|tennis de table\n|tour de table\n|vin de table\n}}\n\n=====Related terms=====\n* {{l|fr|tableau}}\n* {{l|fr|tabulaire}}\n* {{l|fr|tabulation}}\n\n=====Descendants=====\n* {{desc|ht|tab}}\n* {{desc|lou|latab}}\n* {{desc|bor=1|bg|табла}}\n* {{desc|bor=1|mk|табла}}\n* {{desc|bor=1|sh|-}}\n*: {{desc|sclang=1|sh|табла}}\n*: {{desc|sclang=1|sh|tabla}}\n\n===Etymology 2===\nFrom the verb {{m|fr|tabler}}.\n\n====Verb====\n{{head|fr|verb form}}\n\n# {{inflection of|fr|tabler||1//3|s|pres|ind//sub|;|2|s|impr}}\n\n===Further reading===\n* {{R:fr:TLFi}}\n\n===Anagrams===\n* {{l|fr|balte}}, {{l|fr|bêlât}}\n\n{{C|fr|Furniture}}\n\n==Hawaiian Creole==\n\n===Etymology===\n{{der+|hwc|en|table}}.\n\n===Noun===\n{{head|hwc|noun}}\n\n# {{tcl|hwc|table|id=Q14748}}\n#* {{quote-book|hwc|tlr=Joseph Grimes|title=Da Jesus Book: Hawaii Pidgin New Testament|chapter=Matthew 15|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=yKgQAQAAIAAJ|publisher=Wycliffe Bible Translators|year=2000|page=47|pageurl=https://ebible.org/study/content/texts/hwcNT/MT15.html|ISBN=978-0-938978-21-3|text=She say, “Dass right, Boss. But eh, even da dogs unda da '''table''' eat wat fall down from da '''table''', yeah?”|t=“Yes, Lord, but even the dogs can eat the crumbs that fall from their master’s '''table''',” she replied.}}\n\n{{C|hwc|Furniture}}\n\n==Middle English==\n<!--this Middle English entry was created using Template:new enm entry-->\n\n===Alternative forms===\n* {{alt|enm|tabel|tabil|tabul|tabyl|tabyle|tabyll|tabulle|tabele|tabill}}\n\n===Etymology===\nFrom a combination of {{bor|enm|fro|table}} and {{inh|enm|ang|tabele}}, {{m|ang|tabul}}, {{m|ang|tablu}}, {{m|ang|tabule}}, {{m|ang|tabula}}, both from {{der|enm|la|tabula}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{IPA|enm|/ˈtaːbəl/|/ˈtaːblə/}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{enm-noun|tables|pl2=tablen|pl2_qual=early}}\n\n# {{tcl|enm|table|id=Q14748}}\n## The top of a table {{gloss|flat surface of a table for use}}\n## {{lb|enm|figurative}} A [[location]] where one's soul receives nutrition.\n## {{lb|enm|figurative}} A [[serving]] or portion of food.\n# A [[level]] writing [[surface]]:\n## A [[tablet]], especially a [[portable]] one for writing on.\n## An inscribed [[memorial]], dedication, message, or other text; a sign or monument.\n## {{lb|enm|Biblical}} The physical [[Ten Commandments]] handed down from heaven.\n# Any {{gloss|relatively}} level [[surface]]:\n## A wooden pole or board {{gloss|especially behind an altar}}.\n## The board of a [[board game]] {{gloss|often divided in two}}.\n## A [[level]], [[floor]] or [[storey]] {{gloss|of a building}}\n## Such a surface used for [[painting]].\n## {{lb|enm|rare}} A flat piece of [[arable]] land.\n## {{lb|enm|rare|palmistry}} A portion of the hand surrounded by palm lines.\n# A [[glossary]] or [[almanac]]; a reference work or chart of data.\n# A board game similar to [[backgammon]].\n# {{lb|enm|rare}} A flat [[bone]] or fused set of bones.\n\n====Derived terms====\n{{col|enm|rounde table|table rounde}}\n\n====Related terms====\n{{col|enm|tablement|tablen|tabler|tablet}}\n\n====Descendants====\n* {{desc|en|table}} {{see desc}}\n* {{desc|en-geo|tyeble}}\n* {{desc|sco|table}}\n* {{desc|cy|tabl|bor=1}}\n\n====References====\n* {{R:MED Online|entry=tāble |pos=n |id=MED44346 |accessdate=2018-06-27}}\n\n{{C|enm|Agriculture|Board games|Bones|Buildings and structures|Food and drink|Furniture|Religion|Woods|Writing}}\n\n==Old French==\n\n===Etymology===\nFrom {{uder|fro|la|tabula}}.\n\n===Noun===\n{{fro-noun|f}}\n\n# {{tcl|fro|table|id=Q14748}}\n\n====Descendants====\n* {{desctree|fr|table}}\n* {{desc|wa|tåve}}\n* {{desc|bor=1|ga|tábla}}\n* {{desctree|bor=1|enm|table}}\n\n====See also====\n* {{l|fro|nape}}\n\n==Romanian==\n\n===Alternative forms===\n* {{alt|ro|табле||new cyrl}}\n\n===Etymology===\n{{der+|ro|el|τάβλι}}.\n\n===Noun===\n{{ro-noun|f-p}}\n\n# {{plural of|ro|tablă}}\n# [[backgammon]]\n\n====Declension====\n{{ro-noun-f-ă|tabl|n=pl}}\n\n{{C|ro|Board games}}\n\n==Spanish==\n\n===Verb===\n{{head|es|verb form}}\n\n# {{es-verb form of|tablar}}"}}